09/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Three people were injured in a massive brawl among young Serbs that occurred after midnight on Sunday (May 8th) in northern Mitrovica. Police say firearms were also used in the incident. One person was arrested. Mitrovica regional police spokesperson Besim Hoti stressed that Kosovo Police have a strong presence in the north and are patrolling there. This is the second such incident in 48 hours. (RTK, TV 21 - 08/05/11)
